autoProceed.description: If `true`, it will upload as soon as files are added

allowMultipleUploadBatches.description: Whether to allow several upload batches. Default: `True`

maxFileSize.description: Maximum file size in bytes for each individual file

minFileSize.description: Minimum file size in bytes for each individual file

maxTotalFileSize.description:
Maximum file size in bytes for all the files
that can be selected for upload

maxNumberOfFiles.description: Total number of files that can be selected

minNumberOfFiles.description: Minimum number of files that must be selected before the upload

allowedFileTypes.description:
Wildcards `image/*`, or exact mime types `image/jpeg`,
or file extensions `.jpg`

uploadId.description:
The unique identifier for the upload session.
This will be sent to the backend to create a specific sub-folder.

disabled.description: Enabling this option makes the Dashboard grayed-out and non-interactive.

theme.description:
Light or dark theme for the Dashboard.
When it is set to `auto`, it will respect the user’s system settings and switch automatically.
It only can be one of the string ('light', 'dark' and 'auto').

note.description: A string of text to be placed in the Dashboard UI.

size.description: Size of the Dashboard in pixels or percentages.

hideProgressDetails.description: Show or hide progress details in the status bar.

waitForThumbnailsBeforeUpload.description: Whether to wait for all thumbnails to be ready before starting the upload.

showSelectedFiles.description: Show the list of added files with a preview and file information.

singleFileFullScreen.description: When only one file is selected, its preview and meta information will be centered and enlarged.

fileManagerSelectionType.description:
Configure the type of selections allowed when browsing your file system via the file manager selection window.
It only can be one of the string ('files', 'folders' and 'both').

type.name: any
type.raw: { name: string; size: number; type: string; response: ResponseInfo; }[] | undefined

isUploading.description: True when starting upload, False when completed (regardless of success or failure)

id.description: Unique ID to identify this component in Dash callbacks.
